s ($A(\\rm C)$) of CEMP stars in dSph\ngalaxies and find similar behaviour as is seen for Milky Way halo CEMP stars,\nbut highlight that CEMP-$r/s$ stars primarily have very high $A(\\rm C)$ values.\nWe also compare the neutron-capture element abundances of the CEMP-$r/s$ stars\nin our sample to recent $i$-process yields, which provide a good match to the\nderived abundances.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 May 2023 17:58:01 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-04"}
