\n${\\mu}$m). The exclusion of small grains in the upper atmosphere likely has\nimportant consequences for the chemistry due to the deep penetration of\nhigh-energy photons. The addition of a relatively large cavity (ca. 50 au in\nradius) is necessary to explain the strong mid-infrared emission, and to fit\nthe scattered light and continuum observations simultaneously.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 May 2023 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 8 May 2023 08:42:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-05-09"}
